ER", "_links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/pulls/comments/71702431"}, "html": {"href": "https://github.com/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/pull/509#discussion_r71702431"}, "pull_request": {"href": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails-girls-summer-of-code/rgsoc-teams/pulls/509"}}, "body_html": "<p>Hey <a href=\"https://github.com/f3pix\" class=\"user-mention\">@F3PiX</a>, I think chaining <code>where</code> statements constructs <code>AND</code> queries in SQL. Furthermore, I believe the teams association has to be added with <code>includes(:teams).references(:teams)</code>, too.</p>", "body_text": "Hey @F3PiX, I think chaining where statements constructs AND queries in SQL. Furthermore, I believe the teams association has to be added with includes(:teams).references(:teams), too."}